other_tests.findings: Normal sinus rhythm and submillimeter down-sloping ST-segment depressions in leads V3, V4, and V5.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The depressions had decreased in magnitude on electrocardiography performed 3 hours later and had fully resolved on electrocardiography performed 8 hours after presentation.

other_tests.findings: Overall normal left ventricular and right ventricular systolic function with a small, focal area of hypokinesis in the left ventricular inferolateral wall.
Filling defect in the first obtuse marginal branch of the left circumflex coronary artery, presence of sudden, diffuse narrowing of the vessel lumen, and an irregular filling pattern.
The patient was able to exercise for 9 minutes without diagnostic changes on electrocardiography and no chest pain.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The patient has had fleeting episodes of intermittent chest pain but no prolonged episodes since then.
